    "body": "The behavior was initially to save and send cookies from the cookie store. This was changed due to https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/8223 . Thinking back on it, we should expose `LoadFlags` api and follow the second option described above.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfully handle cookies, store them when getting a set-cookie header, and send them back when necessary, automatically (with the possibility of an option to disable this behaviour)\r\n```\r\n\r\n/cc @zcbenz @kevinsawicki thoughts ?"
